## 2. Dataset Overview

### 2.1 Source Files

The archive contains three CSV files covering the same 90-day window at different temporal resolutions:

**`grid_export.csv`** — 34,560 rows × 9 columns, 30-minute intervals  
Records energy injected into the grid and associated financial metrics per inverter. Columns include `export_timestamp`, `inverter_id`, `energy_kwh`, `reactive_power_kvar`, `curtailment_flag`, `tariff_rate`, `revenue_usd`, `power_factor`, and `frequency_hz`.

**`inverter_scada.csv`** — 34,560 rows × 9 columns, 30-minute intervals  
Raw SCADA telemetry from each inverter. Columns include `timestamp`, `inverter_id`, `dc_power_kw`, `ac_power_kw`, `dc_voltage_v`, `dc_current_a`, `module_temp_c`, `inverter_efficiency`, and `status_code`.

**`weather_stations.csv`** — 25,920 rows × 13 columns, 15-minute intervals  
Environmental readings from three geographically distributed stations (WS-North, WS-Central, WS-South). Columns include irradiance components (GHI, DNI, DHI), ambient temperature, wind speed, relative humidity, barometric pressure, solar zenith angle, cloud opacity, and precipitation.

### 2.2 Asset Configuration

| Asset | Count | IDs |
|-------|-------|-----|
| Inverters | 8 | INV-01 through INV-08 |
| Weather stations | 3 | WS-North, WS-Central, WS-South |

### 2.3 Temporal Coverage

All three files cover April 1 to June 29, 2024 — a 90-day period spanning the beginning of the Southern Hemisphere autumn. The weather station readings are at 15-minute granularity (4× per hour), while SCADA and grid export are at 30-minute granularity (2× per hour).

