The spread between the best (INV-08) and worst (INV-03) performer is 16,939 kWh — a 26.6% gap on an identical asset.

### 5.2 INV-03 Degradation Trend

The most significant finding of this analysis is that **INV-03 is not merely underperforming — it is actively degrading within the analysis window.**

Weekly energy output for INV-03 vs. INV-08 (reference):

| Week | INV-03 (kWh) | INV-08 (kWh) | INV-03 vs INV-08 |
|------|-------------|-------------|-----------------|
| Wk 14 | 4,987 | 5,801 | -14% |
| Wk 18 | 5,499 | 6,215 | -12% (peak) |
| Wk 20 | 4,788 | 6,243 | -23% |
| Wk 22 | 4,460 | 6,731 | -34% |
| Wk 26 | 4,060 | 5,577 | -27% |

INV-03's output peaked around week 18 at approximately 5,499 kWh/week and then fell progressively to 4,060 kWh/week by week 26 — a **26% intra-period decline**. INV-08 shows no such trend, and the fleet average remains stable, confirming this is not a weather-driven effect.

### 5.3 DC→AC Conversion Efficiency

Excluding INV-05 (due to the unit mismatch described in §3.5), DC→AC conversion efficiency is remarkably consistent across all inverters:

| Inverter | DC→AC Efficiency |
|----------|-----------------|
| INV-04 | 97.04% |
| INV-03 | 97.01% |
| INV-02 | 97.00% |
| INV-06 | 97.00% |
| INV-08 | 97.00% |
| INV-01 | 96.99% |
| INV-07 | 96.99% |
