GHI increases month-on-month, indicating improving solar resource through the analysis period. The increase from April to June (278 → 299 W/m²) represents a 7.6% improvement in available irradiance — yet total fleet energy output in June (189,701 kWh) was lower than May (201,226 kWh), consistent with INV-03 degradation offsetting the irradiance gain.

### 7.2 Station Comparison

All three weather stations (WS-North, WS-Central, WS-South) report a mean ambient temperature of exactly 24.8°C after unit normalisation. This uniformity across three geographically distributed stations is suspicious and may indicate that the temperature values are being averaged or interpolated at source rather than independently measured.

### 7.3 Generation Window

The generation window (AC power > 0) spans 06:00–18:30, consistent with a site located at approximately 15–25°S latitude during autumn months. The bell-curve peak at 12:00–13:00 is consistent with a fixed-tilt array without tracking.

